    "ideation": "The skull and crossbones emoji shouldn't just be 'dead'; it should be ghastly, hollow, and hauntingly rhythmic. The performance personifies the skull as a physical object and a spectral presence. The eyes are 'hollowed out' using small, centered scales and dark, sunken colors, which then flare with a ghostly white-blue 'soul-fire' as it speaks. The eyelids are used as structural brows, creating an angular, skeletal socket shape. The mouth acts as the 'crossbones' or a rattling jawbone: it moves from a flat, gritted silence to a wide, hollow clatter. The color palette shifts from bone-white to deep void-black and spectral cyan, punctuated by a cold, rattling motion in the mouth wave to simulate a 'death-rattle' laugh.",
